gurmukhi: ਕਰੇ ਜੱਗ ਕੋਟੰ ਜਸੰ ਅਨੇਕ ਲੀਤੇ ॥ ਵਹੈ ਬੀਰ ਬੰਕੇ ਬਲੀ ਕਾਲ ਜੀਤੇ ॥੬੬॥
transliteration: Dare Jagg Kotan Jasan Anek Loote|| Vahai Boor Banke Badoo Kaal Jeete||66||
translation: He, who had performed millions of Yajnas (sacrifices) and erned multi-faceted approbation. Even that winsome warrior (Parasuram) hath been conquered by KAL.66.

gurmukhi: ਕੲੀ ਕੋਟ ਲੀਨੇ ਜਿਨੈ ਦੁਰਗ ਢਾਹੇ ॥ ਕਿਤੇ ਸੂਰਬੀਰਾਨ ਕੇ ਸੈਨ ਗਾਹੇ ॥
transliteration: Kaee Kot Loone Jinai Durg Dhaahe|| Kite Soorbooraan Ke Sain Gadhe||
translation: Those who had conquered millions of forts and razed them. Those who had treaded the forces of innumerable warriors.

gurmukhi: ਕੲੀ ਜੰਗ ਕੀਨੇ ਸੁ ਸਾਕੇ ਪਵਾਰੇ ॥ ਵਹੈ ਦੀਨ ਦੇਖੇ ਗਿਰੇ ਕਾਲ ਮਾਰੇ ॥੬੭॥
transliteration: Kaee Jan Koone Su Saake Pavdare|| Vahai Doon Dekhe Gire Kaal Mdare||67||
translation: Those who had indulged in many wars, events and disputes, I have seen them subdued and killed by KAL.67

gurmukhi: ਜਿਨੈ ਪਾਤਸਾਹੀ ਕਰੀ ਕੋਟ ਜੁਗੰਯਾ ॥ ਰਸੰ ਅਾਨ ਰੱਸੰ ਭਲੀ ਭਾਂਤਿ ਭੁਗੰਯਾ ॥
transliteration: Jinai Paatsaahoo Daroo Kot Jougyaaag|| Rasan Aanrassan Bhaloo Bhaant(i) Bhougyan||
translation: Those who had ruled for millions of ages, and had enjoyed nicely the pleasures and vicious tastes.

gurmukhi: ਵਹੈ ਅੰਤ ਕੋ ਪਾਵ ਨਾਗੇ ਪਧਾਰੇ ॥ ਗਿਰੇ ਦੀਨ ਦੇਖੇ ਹਠੀ ਕਾਲ ਮਾਰੇ ॥੬੮॥
transliteration: Vahai Ant Ko Paav Naage Padhdare|| Gire Doon Dekhe Hathoo Kaal Mdare||68||
translation: They had ultimately gone with naked feet. I have seen them having been subdued, fallen and killed by the persistent KAL.68.

gurmukhi: ਜਿਨੈ ਖੰਡੀਅੰ ਦੰਡ ਧਾਰੰ ਅਪਾਰੰ ॥ ਕਰੇ ਚੰਦ੍ਰਮਾ ਸੂਰ ਚੇਰੇ ਦੁਅਾਰੰ ॥
transliteration: Jinai Khandian Dand Dhaaran Apaaran|| Dare Channdramaa Soor Cdere Duaaran||
translation: He, who had destroyed many kings, He, who had enslaved the moon and the sun in his house.

gurmukhi: ਜਿਨੈ ੲਿੰਦ੍ਰ ਸੇ ਜੀਤ ਕੈ ਛੋਡ ਡਾਰੇ ॥ ਵਹੈ ਦੀਨ ਦੇਖੇ ਗਿਰੇ ਕਾਲ ਮਾਰੇ ॥੬੯॥
transliteration: Jinai Indra Se Jeet Kai Chhodh Ddare|| Vahai Doon Dekhe Gre Kaal Mdare||69||
translation: He (as Ravana), had conquered the god Indra in war and later released him. I have seen (him and Meghnad) being subdued, fallen and killed by KAL.69.

gurmukhi: ਜਿਤੇ ਰਾਮ ਹੂੲੇ ॥ ਸਭੈ ਅੰਤ ਮੂੲੇ ॥
transliteration: Jite Raam Hooe|| Sabhai Ant Moond||
translation: All the Ramas who incarnated, ultimately passed away.

gurmukhi: ਜਿਤੇ ਕ੍ਰਿਸਨ ਹ੍ਵੈਹੈਂ ॥ ਸਭੈ ਅੰਤ ਜੈਹੈਂ ॥੭੦॥
transliteration: Jite Krisan Hvaihain|| Sabhai Ant Jaihain||70||
translation: All the Krishnas, who had incarnated, have all passed away.70.

gurmukhi: ਜਿਤੇ ਦੇਵ ਹੋਸੀ ॥ ਸਭੇ ਅੰਤ ਜਾਸੀ ॥
transliteration: Jite Dev Hosoo|| Sabhe Ant Jaasoo||
translation: All the gods who will come into being in future, they will all ultimately expire.

gurmukhi: ਜਿਤੇ ਬੋਧ ਹ੍ਵੈਹੈਂ ॥ ਸਭੈ ਅੰਤ ਛੈਹੈਂ ॥੭੧॥
transliteration: Jite Bodh Hvaihain|| Sabhai Ant Chhaihain||71||
translation: Alll the Buddhas, who came into being, expired ultimately.71.

gurmukhi: ਜਿਤੇ ਦੲੀਤ ੲੇਸੰ ॥ ਸਭੈ ਅੰਤ ਜਾਯੰ ॥
transliteration: Jite Dev Raayan|| Sabhai Ant Jaayan||
translation: All the god-kings, who came into being, ultimately passed away.

gurmukhi: ਜਿਤੇ ਦੲੀਤ ੲੇਸੰ ॥ ਤਿਤਿਓ ਕਾਲ ਲੇਸੰ ॥੭੨॥
transliteration: Jite Daoot Esan|| Titio Kaal Lesan||72||
translation: All the demon-kings, who came into being, they were all destroyed by KAL.72.
